summary: I've never heard of Monica and you seem like a huge stan, what are the best parts about her?
question: I've never heard of Monica and you seem like a huge stan, what are the best parts about her?
answer:
God I love Monica you have no idea ajdjjdkd. So Monica Rambeau was the first female Captain Marvel and I was first introduced to her in literally a random ass avengers comic I bought because it had She-Hulk in it. She was the leader (they called her chairperson) of the avengers and like cool as hell. Like she turned into any kind of light or energy, she could travel the whole world is less time than it would take for me to get out of bed, and she was just the most badass character ever. Like the first moment I saw her I was like shes my new favorite.
Honestly my favorite things about her is she’s unapologetic, she takes no ones’s shit, and shes just so cool. I’ve read some weird comics cuz she was in them (some were actually really good like Nextwave: Agents of H.A.T.E. was surprisingly fun)
I think definitely what I love the most about her was that she was so groundbreaking. So Captain Marvel was originally a white man and he wasnt super popular he really was just a name holder cuz Marvel didnt want D.C. to take the name so when they retired him Monica was introduced. Everything about Monica was so different from him. She was a black woman that was created in the 80s and given a position of power. She was the first black woman to be on the avengers and the first black woman to lead them. And like not only was she the progressive she was powerful. She turned into energy! She could disappear as light, become gamma radiation, she could blind people, become radio waves and transmit messages, become microwaves and melt someone. Her powers are nearly limitless if you’re creative enough.
God I love her so much I could talk about her all day!

body:
(I know you guys hate me for this)

Deadpool as Regina George

“That is the ugliest f-ing skirt I’ve ever seen.”

Steve Rogers as Cady Heron


“Grool. I meant to say great but then I started to say cool.”

Captain Marvel as Aaron Samuels

“Your face smells like peppermint”

Ant-Man as Gretchen Wieners

“I’m sorry that people are so jealous of me. But I can’t help it that I’m popular.” 

Star-lord as Karen Smith

“I’m kind of psychic. I have a fifth sense… It’s like I have ESPN or something. My breasts can tell when it’s gonna rain.”

Loki as Janis Ian

“Student: Nice wig, Janis. What’s it made of?
Janis Ian: Your mom’s chest hair!”

Iron-man as Mrs.George

“Can I get you guys anything? Some snacks? A condom? Let me know! Oh, God love ya.”

Black Widow as Ms.Norbury

“Oh, hi. Did you wanna buy some drugs?”

Thor as Damian

“That’s why her hair is so big. It’s full of secrets”

blog.name: anniesinspirations
blog.title: Annie's Inspiration
blog.description:
These are the things that inspire me, the quotes that give me hope, the artwork I do to encourage myself. 
May they so the same for you.

summary: I didn't plan to share these. I didn't schedule them or write some long winded description. I drew these today. These are what I...
body:
These aren’t colored yet.

I didn’t plan to share these. I didn’t schedule them or write some long winded description. I drew these today. These are what I needed today.

I needed the inspirational words of Agent Carter.

I needed to remember how much value I have inherently as a human being.

I needed the inspirational being of Captain Marvel.

I needed the reminder that I can be human and compassionate and oh so strong.

I needed the words of my mother.

I needed to remember that I am the only force in life I have full control over.

This collection of pictures, this collection of words, this collection of women saved me from so much pain today.

Without them, I may have found myself much worse off.

Without them, I may have wallowed in selfpity. Without them, I may have allowed the hurtful words and actions of another human being to control me.

Whenever I manage to color all three, I’ll surely share the final results. But as for now, I just need to remember this:

Be the bigger person.

Take the higher road.

Know your value.
